The table of parties in power in the 20th C. is constructed 
by a table, width 100 percent, width of each TD element defined
in percent, with each one percent for one year.
The table for the period since 1945 uses a table with
widths defined absolutely in pixels. Since 1 pixel = 1 year
would make it only 61 wide, each year must be represented 
by n pixels. The simplest solution would be to multiply by
ten, but this would make the table 610 wide, making the page 
too large for browsers set to the minimum 600 x 400 view - which
would be contrary to our "any browser" approach. So each year is
represented by 9 pixels. -->
